Kisangani lies in the Upper Congo Rapids Ecoregion (FEOW #539) (
Thieme et al . 2005
;
Abell et al . 2008
). The field notes of Herbert Lang on the habitat of P. kisangani sp. nov. from Kisangani provided by Rathbun (1921: 415) indicate that although this species is found in large rivers, it favours shallow waters near river banks where drifting logs jam. At the Boyoma Falls near Kisangani these crabs were common above and below the cataracts, while in the Tshopo River crabs were abundant among the rocks and boulder fields above the Tshopo Falls, but were absent below the falls where the water was shallow and had a sandy substrate.

